From 7a5488fe76ee9bf753c63e7be9fb5bc1340ecd71 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Govindaraj Saminathan <gsaminat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Oct 2025 16:24:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: hostapd:Reset SA-Query Timeout on Re-Auth
 for UNASSOC STA

Some STAs send a new Authentication frame after a PMF SA‑Query timeout.
When this happens, hostapd removes the previously associated STA and creates
a new UNASSOC entry, but the sa_query_timed_out flag remains set.

As a result, when the next Association frame arrives, the UNASSOC MLD STA may
be removed and only a partner link is attempted—without a valid MLD context,
which leading to link rejection (0x008b) and single‑link fallback.

Clear the SA‑Query timeout state when handling Authentication for a
re‑added STA (transitioning to UNASSOC) so that the subsequent Association
can proceed with the preserved MLD context.

Patch-dependency: r68-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-Handle-Dynamic-link-addr-change-for-co.patch

Signed-off-by: Govindaraj Saminathan <gsaminat@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
index 4a889ca..7cbf108 100644
--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -3459,6 +3459,8 @@ static void handle_auth(struct hostapd_data *hapd,
 					resp = WLAN_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED_FAILURE;
 					goto fail;
 				}
+				/*reset sa query timed out flag - since it is readded and moved to unassoc state*/
+				sta->sa_query_timed_out = 0;
 			}
 		}
 #endif /* CONFIG_IEEE80211BE */
